-- HRT Participacoes May Raise $1.8 Billion in Brazil Initial Public Offering
-- B y   L a u r a   P r i c e
-- 2010-10-07T10:15:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/hrt-participacoes-may-raise-1-8-billion-in-brazil-initial-public-offering.html
HRT Participacoes em Petroleo SA , a
Brazilian oil and gas exploration company, may raise as much as
2.97 billion reais ($1.77 billion) in an initial public
offering.  HRT, based in Rio de Janeiro, and its shareholders plan to
offer as many as 1.63 million shares. The offering may be priced
from 1,050 reais to 1,350 reais per share, HRT said in a
preliminary prospectus in Valor Economico newspaper today. The
company may also sell as many as 567,000 shares should an over-
allotment option be exercised in full.  HRT holds exploration rights in onshore blocks in the
 Brazilian basins  of  Solimoes , Espirito Santo, Reconcavo and Rio
do Peixe and offshore blocks in the Walvis and Orange basins in
Namibia, according to a separate prospectus filed to  Brazil’s
securities regulator . The proceeds of the sale will be invested
in exploration, development and infrastructure, according to the
prospectus.  The shares may be priced on Oct. 21 and start trading in
Sao Paulo on Oct. 25, HRT said. Credit Suisse Group AG’s local
unit is coordinating the sale with Goldman Sachs Group Inc. and
Citigroup Inc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
